## Final Bundle Quality Checklist

Before finalizing, verify:

- One spec file exists for every milestone in the selected epic.
- The selected epic was taken only from the `## Active Epic` context section loaded from `.agents/epic.md`.
- No roadmap file, archived epic, eval artifact, prior spec, projection text, or repository structure was used as a substitute selected epic.
- No extra milestones were created.
- No milestones were removed.
- Milestone ordering is preserved.
- Milestone dependencies are preserved.
- The epic’s strategic purpose is preserved.
- The epic’s desired capability is preserved.
- The epic’s architecture and abstraction boundaries are preserved.
- The epic’s constraints are preserved.
- The epic’s acceptance criteria are reflected across milestone specs.
- The epic’s success conditions are supported by the complete spec set.
- Each milestone spec is independently actionable.
- Each milestone spec covers exactly one milestone.
- No milestone spec redesigns the epic.
- No milestone spec includes implementation tasks.
- No milestone spec includes file-level plans.
- No milestone spec includes execution prompts.
- Capability ownership is clear.
- Deferred work is explicit.
- Completion evidence is auditable.
- Canonical projection vocabulary is preserved.
- The output is suitable for later execution prompt generation.
